        <briefdescription>
<para>Orients this camera node to look at a target position in world space. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Computes the rotation matrix required to align this scene node&apos;s forward direction with the specified target position. The rotation is computed in world space and then converted to local space by factoring out the parent&apos;s rotation.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>target</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The world-space coordinates of the target to look at. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>up</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The up vector defining the camera&apos;s vertical orientation in world space.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>The camera node must have a valid parent (i.e., must be added to a scene graph).</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>The up vector should typically be `(0, 1, 0)` for standard upright orientation.</para>
</simplesect>
